<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="194" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,551,758]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194">
The original collection cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[505,690,551,578]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194" pagination="226 - 228" refId="ref7178" refString="Bentham, G. (1870) Caesalpinieae. In: von Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (Eds.) Flora Brasiliensis 15 (2). F. Fleischer, Leipzig, pp. 226 - 228." type="book chapter" year="1870">Bentham (1870)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authority=", Spruce 2021" authorityName=", Spruce" authorityYear="2021" box="[740,1046,551,578]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="194" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucantha">
<emphasis box="[740,884,551,577]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="194">E. leucantha</emphasis>
, Spruce 2021
</taxonomicName>
, combined collections made in two different dates: 
<date box="[315,495,587,614]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194" value="1851-12">December 1851</date>
and 
<date box="[553,708,587,614]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194" value="1852-01">January 1852</date>
. However, in order to comprise a single gathering the specimens need to be collected on the same date (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[593,823,623,650]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194" refId="ref8934" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[693,752,623,649]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="194">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, Spruce 2021 must be considered two different collections. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[309,492,659,686]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194" pagination="226 - 228" refId="ref7178" refString="Bentham, G. (1870) Caesalpinieae. In: von Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (Eds.) Flora Brasiliensis 15 (2). F. Fleischer, Leipzig, pp. 226 - 228." type="book chapter" year="1870">Bentham (1870)</bibRefCitation>
did not specify the collection date of Spruce 2021, the exsiccate K000555107 with a handwritten annotation by Spruce is not the 
<typeStatus box="[635,733,695,721]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194">holotype</typeStatus>
as informed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cowan, R. S." box="[917,1082,695,722]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194" pagination="1 - 45" refId="ref7339" refString="Cowan, R. S. (1975) Monograph of the genus Eperua (Leguminosae: Caesalpinioideae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 28: 1 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 0081024 X. 28" type="journal article" year="1975">Cowan (1975)</bibRefCitation>
. We correct here Cowan’s use of 
<typeStatus box="[136,234,731,757]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194">holotype</typeStatus>
to 
<typeStatus box="[270,376,731,757]" pageId="5" pageNumber="194">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
